{
  "type": "feat",
  "name": "Sprouting Palms",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><span class=\"va-quotation-text\"><em>Trying to escape from your Intoxicating Petals is a Fool's Errand.</em></span></p><p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Two @UUID[Compendium.pf1-pow.disciplines.Item.YKyesqqDVNSpFBgN]{Fool's Errand} maneuvers, two @UUID[Compendium.pf1-pow.disciplines.Item.iwfbEXyacCnVLEoH]{Intoxicating Petal} maneuvers</p><p><strong>Benefit:</strong> Creatures you have locked that are not sprouted are treated as having [sprout 0].</p><p>Whenever you would apply sprout to a creature within your natural reach, you may attempt to lock that creature instead.</p><p>You may treat unarmed strikes as discipline weapons for Intoxicating Petal maneuvers.</p>",
